parameter.name: SEP9000p
parameter.longDescription: SEPP_I2C_PAYLOAD_BUS_SEPP_TSENSE1_TEMP Temperature Sensor 1- Temperature Register Value/The Temperature Register of the TMP112 device is configured as a 12-bit read-only register by default (EM = 0)- or as a 13-bit read-only register (EM = 1) that stores the output of the most recent conversion./For SEPP it is sufficient to use 12-bit mode only./Two bytes must be read to obtain the last temperature value. Byte 1 is the most significant byte (MSB)- followed by byte 2- the least significant byte (LSB). The first 12 bits (13 bits in extended mode) are used to indicate temperature./ Temperature Register bits: T11- T10- T9- T8- ...
